1810<h2>

1811What type of Sink are You Looking For?</h2>

1812

1813

1814<p>

1815With various styles and materials available for sinks, we want to give you a quick overview of the types you&rsquo;ll find at Vevano Home.</p>

1816

1817

1818<h3>

1819Sink Types:</h3>

1820

1821

1822<ul>

1823

1824 <li>

1825<em>

1826<strong>

1827Kitchen sinks</strong>

1828</em>

1829 include farmhouse (also known as apron), drop-in, undermount, single basin, double basin, and commercial style sinks. We also carry a selection of garbage disposals and accessories.&nbsp;</li>

1830

1831 <li>

1832<em>

1833<strong>

1834Bathroom sinks</strong>

1835</em>

1836 include undermount, drop-in, vessel sink, pedestal style, wall mount, integrated, console, and accessories.&nbsp;</li>

1837

1838 <li>

1839<em>

1840<strong>

1841Laundry sinks</strong>

1842</em>

1843 include undermount, drop-in, apron style, single basin, double basin, freestanding, wall mount, and accessories.&nbsp;</li>

1844

1845</ul>

1846

1847

1848<p>

1849Contact us via chat or send an email to <a href="mailto:design@vevano.com" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">

1850<u>

1851design@vevano.com</u>

1852</a>

1853 with any questions you may have.&nbsp;</p>

1854

1855

1856<h3>

1857<strong>

1858Which Sink is Best for You?</strong>

1859&nbsp;</h3>

1860

1861

1862<p>

1863Wondering which sink style is the best fit for you? Here&rsquo;s a quick run-down of the styles we carry.&nbsp;</p>

1864

1865

1866<ul>

1867

1868 <li>

1869<strong>

1870Undermount &ndash;</strong>

1871 This means countertop is on top of the sink, instead of the sink being placed on top on the counter. It allows for easy cleanup and maintenance.&nbsp;</li>

1872

1873 <li>

1874<strong>

1875Drop-in Mount &ndash;</strong>

1876 This style is placed in the cutout for the sink, with the edges overlapping on top of the counter.&nbsp;</li>

1877

1878 <li>

1879<strong>

1880Farmhouse</strong>

1881 &ndash; Also known as apron sinks, this style features an exposed front of the sink with room to lean directly over the sink.&nbsp;</li>

1882

1883 <li>

1884<strong>

1885Single Basin</strong>

1886 &ndash; This refers sinks that have one basin, or bowl. It provides a larger area to wash dishes.&nbsp;</li>

1887

1888 <li>

1889<strong>

1890Double Basin</strong>

1891 &ndash; Instead of a single large bowl, double basins divide the sink into two compartments.&nbsp;</li>

1892

1893 <li>

1894<strong>

1895Commercial</strong>

1896 &ndash; Commercial sinks are rated for the increased use a commercial area would give, ideal for maximum durability.&nbsp;</li>

1897

1898 <li>

1899<strong>

1900Vessel &ndash;</strong>

1901 A vessel sink is a large bowl that sits on top of the countertop, instead of within it. It&rsquo;s designed to be used with a <em>

1902<strong>

1903vessel faucet</strong>

1904</em>

1905.&nbsp;</li>

1906

1907 <li>

1908<strong>

1909Pedestal</strong>

1910 &ndash; A pedestal sink is the sink basin as well as the pedestal together, typically mounted to a wall.&nbsp;</li>

1911

1912 <li>

1913<strong>

1914Wall Mount</strong>

1915 &ndash; These are mounted directly to the wall, freeing up floor space below.&nbsp;</li>

1916

1917 <li>

1918<strong>

1919Integrated &ndash;</strong>

1920 Integrated means the sink is made from the same material as the countertop for a seamless transition.&nbsp;</li>

1921

1922 <li>

1923<strong>

1924Console &ndash;</strong>

1925 This style is mounted to the wall or freestanding, available with two legs or four legs for additional support.&nbsp;</li>

1926

1927 <li>

1928<strong>

1929Freestanding &ndash;</strong>

1930 This type stands on its own, not requiring additional support like the console does.&nbsp;</li>

1931

1932</ul>

1933
